 The essence of human/ higher level learning is developing the skill 
to discriminate patterns and identify shared 
characteristics across events (stimuli).

 Memorization - the regurgitation of facts - 
is considered the lowest level of learning.

Why, then, are students encouraged to learn CS?
Because the world is rapidly becoming more technologically advanced, 
and we need people who can work on and manage the machines.

What should students learn from CS?
We should learn how to program in Java, and solve problems.
